\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 26.       Dactylis}        L.
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By †T.G. Tutin. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perennials. Leaves flat or involute. Inflorescence a panicle with spikelets in dense clusters on the patent to erect branches. Spikelets laterally compressed, with 2-5 florets. Glumes subequal, keeled, somewhat curved, the lower 1-, the upper 3-veined. Lemma 5-veined, chartaceous, mucronate or shortly awned at apex. Palea about as long as lemma.
\par

